         A, B and C are classes
         A is a super class. B is a sub class of A. C is a sub class of B.
          
          I)  Create three methods in each class, 2 methods are specific to each class and third
              method (override method) should be in all three Classes A, B and C ?
          
          Ans.         class A {
                         void get (int a) {
                                      this.a = a;
                                        }
                       class B extends A {
                                      this.b = b;
                                        }
                            void put()  {
                                System.out.println("a=". +a);
                                System.out.println("b=", +b);
                                      }
                                    }
                        class C extends  A {
                                         int c;
                                void get(int c) {
                                        this.c = c;
                                            }
                                void put() {
                                      System.out.println("a=", +a);
                                      System.out.println("b=", +b);
                                          }
                                        }
                               
                II)   Create a class with main method. Create an object for each class A, B and C in main 
                      method and call every method of each class using its own object/instance ?
                   
                Ans.         class A {
                         void get (int a) {
                                      this.a = a;
                                        }
                                       }
                       class B extends A {
                                      int b;
                               void get(int b)  {
                                      this.b = b;
                                        }
                                      }
                        class C extends  B {
                                         int c;
                                void cal(int c) {
                                        this.c = c;
                                        c = a +b;
                                            }
                                void put() {
                                      System.out.println("a=", +a);
                                      System.out.println("b=", +b);
                                      System.out.println("c=", +c);
                                          }
                                        }
                       class Mn  {
                       public static void main(String[] args)  {
                                    A.obj1 = new A();
                                    B.obj2 = new B();
                                    C.obj3 = new C();
                                    obj1.get a(5);
                                    obj2.get b(7);
                                    obj3.calc();
                                    obj3.put();
                                  }
                                }
                             
                   III)   Runtime Polymorphism with Data Members/Instance variables, Repeat the above process only for data members ?
                   
                   Ans.                 class Bike{  
                                          int speedlimit=90;  
                                                 }  
                                        class Honda3 extends Bike{  
                                           int speedlimit=150;  
                                                } 
                                    public static void main(String args[]){  
                                            Bike obj=new Honda3();  
                                    System.out.println(obj.speedlimit);  
                                               }  
                                    
              
          
     
